cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with facial analysis from video sequences using deep learning techniques, specifically 3D CNNs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves transfer learning and joint supervised learning, which are common techniques in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The application of the framework in the medical domain suggests a possible fit in cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of video sequences and deep learning for motion recognition and grading also suggests a possible fit in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of neural networks for prediction and classification suggests a possible fit in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
